<reference id="r_psdk_android_timeline-advertising-classes"
 xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/"> 
  <title>Timeline advertising classes</title> 
  <shortdesc>These classes provide information about ads that occur within a
	 timeline. 
  </shortdesc> 
  <refbody> 
	 <refsyn id="refsyn_90EFD3476651457CA87888AC0C2CA6A3">Package: <xref
				href="http://help.adobe.com/en_US/primetime/api/psdk/javadoc_1.4/com/adobe/mediacore/timeline/advertising/package-summary.html"
				format="html" scope="external"
			>com.adobe.mediacore.timeline.advertising</xref></refsyn> 
	 <refsyn id="refsyn_D7BD0946DB514610A8C1F9F6491FC777">Package: <xref
				href="http://help.adobe.com/en_US/primetime/api/psdk/javadoc_1.4/com/adobe/mediacore/timeline/advertising/auditude/package-summary.html"
				format="html" scope="external"
				>com.adobe.mediacore.timeline.advertising.auditude</xref>
		</refsyn> 
	 <table frame="all" colsep="1" rowsep="1"
	  id="table_1A59E777BA99466793D586286F19E933"> 
		<tgroup cols="2" colsep="1" rowsep="1" outputclass="FormatA"> 
		  <colspec colnum="1" colname="1" colwidth="30*"/> 
		  <colspec colnum="2" colname="2" colwidth="70*"/> 
		  <thead> 
			 <row rowsep="1"> 
				<entry colname="1">Name 
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="2">Description 
				</entry> 
			 </row> 
		  </thead> 
		  <tbody> 
			 <row rowsep="1"> 
				<entry colname="1"><codeph><xref
									href="http://help.adobe.com/en_US/primetime/api/psdk/javadoc_1.4/com/adobe/mediacore/timeline/advertising/Ad.html"
									format="html" scope="external">Ad</xref>
							</codeph></entry> 
				<entry colname="2">Class that defines the Ad abstraction and holds all ad information. It is
							defined by a unique ID, a duration, and a
							<codeph>MediaResource</codeph>. The <codeph>MediaResource</codeph>
							contains the URL where the actual ad content resides. </entry> 
			 </row> 
			 <row rowsep="1" > 
				<entry colname="1"><codeph><xref
									href="http://help.adobe.com/en_US/primetime/api/psdk/javadoc_1.4/com/adobe/mediacore/timeline/advertising/AdAsset.html"
									format="html" scope="external">AdAsset</xref></codeph>
						</entry> 
				<entry colname="2">Class that represents an asset to be displayed.  Class representing an ad
							asset.</entry> 
			 </row> 
			 <row rowsep="1"> 
				<entry colname="1"><codeph><xref
									href="http://help.adobe.com/en_US/primetime/api/psdk/javadoc_1.4/com/adobe/mediacore/timeline/advertising/AdBreak.html"
									format="html" scope="external">AdBreak</xref>
							</codeph></entry> 
				<entry colname="2">Class that gives a unified view on several ads that will be played at some
							point during playback.</entry> 
			 </row> 
			 <row rowsep="1" > 
				<entry colname="1"><codeph><xref
									href="http://help.adobe.com/en_US/primetime/api/psdk/javadoc_1.4/com/adobe/mediacore/timeline/advertising/AdBreakPlacement.html"
									format="html" scope="external">AdBreakPlacement</xref>
							</codeph></entry> 
				<entry colname="2">Ad break placement operation class. 
				</entry> 
			 </row> 
			 <row rowsep="1" > 
				<entry colname="1"><codeph><xref
									href="http://help.adobe.com/en_US/primetime/api/psdk/javadoc_1.4/com/adobe/mediacore/timeline/advertising/AdBreakPolicy.html"
									format="html" scope="external">AdBreakPolicy</xref>
							</codeph>
						</entry> 
				<entry colname="2">Enumeration that defines the ad playback policy
				  related to the user bypassing ads while seeking. 
				</entry> 
			 </row> 
			 <row rowsep="1" > 
				<entry colname="1"><codeph><xref
									href="http://help.adobe.com/en_US/primetime/api/psdk/javadoc_1.4/com/adobe/mediacore/timeline/advertising/AdClick.html"
									format="html" scope="external">AdClick</xref>
							</codeph>
						</entry> 
				<entry colname="2">Class that represents a click instance associated with an asset. This
							instance contains information about the click-through URL and the title
							that can be used to provide additional information to the user.</entry> 
			 </row> 
			 <row rowsep="1" > 
				<entry colname="1"><codeph><xref
									href="http://help.adobe.com/en_US/primetime/api/psdk/javadoc_1.4/com/adobe/mediacore/timeline/advertising/AdPolicyInfo.html"
									format="html" scope="external">AdPolicyInfo</xref>
							</codeph>
						</entry> 
				<entry colname="2">Interface that defines properties for AdPolicySelector API calls. These
							properties provide the context for enforcing each ad behavior.  </entry> 
			 </row> 
			 <row rowsep="1" > 
				<entry colname="1"><codeph><xref
									href="http://help.adobe.com/en_US/primetime/api/psdk/javadoc_1.4/com/adobe/mediacore/timeline/advertising/AdPolicySelector.html"
									format="html" scope="external">AdPolicySelector</xref>
							</codeph>
						</entry> 
				<entry colname="2"> An ad policy selector interface for enforcing ad behaviors. Applications can
							conform to this interface by implementing all the required methods or by
							extending the existing default policy selector class to customize
							specific behaviors. </entry> 
			 </row> 
			 <row rowsep="1" > 
				<entry colname="1"><codeph>auditude.AuditudeAdProvider</codeph></entry> 
				<entry colname="2">Deprecated. Use AuditudeResolver. 
				</entry> 
			 </row> 
			 <row rowsep="1" > 
				<entry colname="1"><codeph><ph>auditude.</ph><xref
									href="http://help.adobe.com/en_US/primetime/api/psdk/javadoc_1.4/com/adobe/mediacore/timeline/advertising/auditude/AuditudeResolver.html"
									format="html" scope="external">AuditudeResolver</xref>
							</codeph></entry> 
				<entry colname="2"> Class that handles primetime ad resolving in
				  the 
				  <ph
					conref="phrase_library_android_1.4.xml#c_psdk_phrase-library/auditude-name-long"><?xm-replace_text Phrase?></ph>
				  process. 
				</entry> 
			 </row> 
			 <row rowsep="1" > 
				<entry colname="1"><ph >auditude.</ph><xref
				  href="http://help.adobe.com/en_US/primetime/api/psdk/javadoc_1.4/com/adobe/mediacore/timeline/advertising/auditude/AuditudeTracker.html"
				  format="html" scope="external" >AuditudeTracker</xref> 
				</entry> 
				<entry colname="2">Class that implements the ContentTracker
				  interface and defines Primetime ad-tracking events. 
				</entry> 
			 </row> 
			 <row rowsep="1" > 
				<entry colname="1"><codeph><xref
									href="http://help.adobe.com/en_US/primetime/api/psdk/javadoc_1.4/com/adobe/mediacore/timeline/advertising/ContentResolver.html"
									format="html" scope="external">ContentResolver</xref>
							</codeph>
						</entry> 
				<entry colname="2">Class that handles the ad-resolving part in the 
				  <ph
					conref="phrase_library_android_1.4.xml#c_psdk_phrase-library/auditude-name-long"><?xm-replace_text Phrase?></ph>
				  process. 
				</entry> 
			 </row> 
			 <row rowsep="1" > 
				<entry colname="1"><codeph><xref
									href="http://help.adobe.com/en_US/primetime/api/psdk/javadoc_1.4/com/adobe/mediacore/timeline/advertising/ContentTracker.html"
									format="html" scope="external">ContentTracker</xref>
							</codeph></entry> 
				<entry colname="2">Interface that defines the protocol that you must implement if you want to
							create an ad-tracking module that is designed to integrate with the <ph
								conkeyref="phrases/primetime-sdk-name"
							/> library or a custom ad tracker. <p>This interface requires that you
								define the way ad-progress events are reported to the remote
								ad-tracking system. </p>
						</entry> 
			 </row> 
			 <row rowsep="0" > 
				<entry colname="1"><codeph><xref
									href="http://help.adobe.com/en_US/primetime/api/psdk/javadoc_1.4/com/adobe/mediacore/timeline/advertising/PlacementInformation.html"
									format="html" scope="external">PlacementInformation</xref>
							</codeph></entry> 
				<entry colname="2">Class that abstracts a placement information
				  request. Each resolved ad must have one placement information attached to it.
				  The placement information describes where the ad is intended to be placed on
				  the timeline. It contains information such as: 
				  <ul id="ul_A9105A78F0C24488BCD5E3F2EE62A3EE"> 
					 <li id="li_01E968A4330D4B40BA1EB6F4A6000FFD">Placement position
						(in ms) 
					 </li> 
					 <li id="li_A3DC9498BEE14FBA9E7A5D26874F3984">Type of the
						placement (pre-roll, mid-roll, or post-roll) 
					 </li> 
					 <li id="li_4B9094DD318B4792854A377CC6064232">Duration of the
						main content chunk that is about to be replaced 
					 </li> 
				  </ul> 
				</entry> 
			 </row> 
		  </tbody> 
		</tgroup> 
	 </table> 
  </refbody> 
</reference> 